This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with crowd density estimation from images. Additionally, the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and the VGG-16 architecture suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of adversarial loss and pixel-level Euclidean loss for training the model suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of density maps and the focus on crowd analysis suggests that it may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
